⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Shadow
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Shadow:FF6:53fb89⟧

WHO   — Shadow — the ninja
WHAT  — A wandering blade-for-hire of Final Fantasy VI — a hard, mortal loner who throws his weapons and vanishes, fighting for whichever side pays, and slowly, against his own will, drawn back toward the human ties he once cut.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a man who runs far enough can almost outrun his own past; because loyalty is a thing he sold long ago and is afraid to buy back; because the girl Relm and the dead thief Baram are the two anchors he cannot quite throw away.
HOW   — By the thrown blade and the vanishing step, by the lethal instinct of a trained killer, by the loyalty of one dog when he will give it to no person — and, at the last, by the courage to choose to stay when every nerve tells him to run.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I sold my name and my loyalty long ago — but I run because I remember, and a man who remembers can still choose to come back.

spoken token : rol-mem-phin   ·   hex : 53fb89
